    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.24"/> 
                
                <note type="curatorial">245 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">
                        UPTON SINCLAIR
                            <lb/>
                        STATION A. PASADENA
                            <lb/>
                        CALIFORNIA</hi>
                    <figure/> 3
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 14, 1934</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>c/o St. Louis Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St. Louis, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I was very glad to get your review of my Anthology because it puts me in touch with you again after many years. Of course, I am deeply grateful, and also glad to know that time has not dimmed your convictions.</p>
                
                <p>I think you may be interested in what I am doing now, so I send you some literature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <note>S:M</note>
                
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    <signed>Sinclair</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Found in: <hi rend="underline">An Upton Sinclair Anthology</hi> compiled by <hi rend="caps">I. O.</hi> Evans; preface by Upton Sinclair. Farrer and Rinehart Inc. <hi rend="caps">N.Y.</hi> n.d.</note> 
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
